---
description: Python interpreter and tooling (Always)
globs:
  alwaysApply: true
---

- Use the Python interpreter at `${env:HOME}/.virtualenvs/lastversion/bin/python` for all Python execution in this workspace.
- When running tests, use: `${env:HOME}/.virtualenvs/lastversion/bin/python -m pytest` (not bare `pytest`).
- When invoking scripts or modules (formatters, linters, CLI tools), call them via the interpreter: `${env:HOME}/.virtualenvs/lastversion/bin/python -m <module>`.
- Prefer this interpreter for local runs, CI, and any automation unless explicitly overridden.
- Source `~/.secrets` prior to running tests, as this file contains the required API tokens.
- Run pylint via the interpreter before commits/PRs: `${env:HOME}/.virtualenvs/lastversion/bin/python -m pylint src tests`.
- Use project-local config if present (e.g., `pyproject.toml` or `pylintrc`).
